description_html:
This gallery contains images of the personalities of some of the wildlings who live north of the wall on the show Game of Thrones.

Click on one of the images on this page to see a full-sized image on its own page.
story_html:
Make it personal (first and second person ok), preferably with a beginning, middle, and end.

To keep up to date, follow this site on social media or subscribe to the Artsy Visions Monthly Newsletter!

image_list.title: Ygritte
image_list.subtitle_html: Jon Snow's Wildling Lover
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Ygritte's spiritual portrait shows she is realistic and can remain cool and calm when threatened.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Green in Ygritte's spiritual portrait represents her dominant personality trait, her moderate preference for being more objective than subjective.  In Extraverts, the dominant trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long vertical line to represent this, because it is the side of their personality that is most evident.  She demonstrated this preference in the way she murdered citizens in cold blood during raids in the north of Westeros.
image_list.explain_aux: The Yellow in Ygritte's spiritual portrait represents her auxiliary personality trait, her strong preference for being realistic.  In Extraverts, the auxiliary trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a horizontal line to represent this.

image_list.title: Tormund Giantsbane
image_list.subtitle_html: Wildling Leader and Ally of Jon Snow
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Tormund's spiritual portrait shows he is cool, objective, and realistic.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Green in this spiritual portrait represents X's dominant personality trait, Thinking: objectivity; rationality; cool-headedness; very slight/moderate/strong preference for logic/reason/objectivity over emotion/empathy/subjectivity; their very slight/moderate/strong preference for the/tendency to be more logical/rational/objective over the emotional/personal/subjective.

The Green in X's spiritual portrait represents their dominant personality trait, their very slight/moderate/strong preference for making logical/rational/objective rather than emotional/personal/subjective decisions; their very slight/moderate/strong preference for being/tendency to be more logical/rational/objective rather than emotional/personal/subjective.
image_list.explain_dom_constant: In Introverts, the dominant trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long horizontal line to represent this.  He/She demonstrates/exhibits this trait in their (note that is easier to find examples of decisions than perceptions!) ....
image_list.explain_dom_very_slight_preference: It's important to note this preference/tendency is very slight, and X can be quite _____ in some situations/when the situation calls for it.
image_list.explain_aux: The Yellow in this spiritual portrait represents X's auxiliary personality trait, Sensing: pragmatism; pragmatic; practical; realism; realistic; outlook; openness to new experiences; very slight/moderate/strong preference for facts over ideas.

The Yellow in X's spiritual portrait represents their auxiliary personality trait, their very slight/moderate/strong preference for seeing/tendency to see the world more in terms of facts rather than of ideas; need for sensual stimulation.
image_list.explain_aux_constant: In Introverts, the auxiliary trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a vertical line to represent this, because it is more evident than the dominant function.  He/She demonstrates/exhibits this trait in their (note that is easier to find examples of decisions than perceptions!) ....
